## 1.3 Variables & Data Types

### Primitive Data Types (8 Types)

| Type | Size | Range | Example |
|------|------|-------|---------|
| byte | 1 byte | -128 to 127 | `byte b = 10;` |
| short | 2 bytes | -32,768 to 32,767 | `short s = 1000;` |
| int | 4 bytes | -2B to 2B | `int i = 100000;` |
| long | 8 bytes | -9.2Q to 9.2Q | `long l = 1000L;` |
| float | 4 bytes | ±3.4E38 | `float f = 5.5f;` |
| double | 8 bytes | ±1.7E308 | `double d = 5.5;` |
| char | 2 bytes | 0 to 65535 | `char c = 'A';` |
| boolean | 1 bit | true/false | `boolean b = true;` |

### Type Casting

**Implicit (Automatic) Casting:**
```java
int i = 10;
long l = i;              // Automatic - smaller to larger
double d = i;            // Automatic - int to double
```

**Explicit (Manual) Casting:**
```java
double d = 10.5;
int i = (int) d;         // Explicit - result: i = 10
```

