# PART 2: OBJECT-ORIENTED PROGRAMMING (INTERMEDIATE LEVEL)

## 2.1 Classes and Objects

### Basic Class Structure

```java
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int rollNumber;
    private double gpa;
    
    public Student(String name, int rollNumber, double gpa) {
        this.name = name;
        this.rollNumber = rollNumber;
        this.gpa = Math.min(4.0, Math.max(0, gpa));
    }
    
    public String getName() { return name; }
    public int getRollNumber() { return rollNumber; }
    public double getGPA() { return gpa; }
    
    public void setGPA(double newGPA) {
        this.gpa = Math.min(4.0, Math.max(0, newGPA));
    }
    
    public void displayInfo() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Roll: " + rollNumber);
        System.out.println("GPA: " + String.format("%.2f", gpa));
    }
}
```

### Creating Objects

```java
Student student1 = new Student("Alice", 101, 3.8);
Student student2 = new Student("Bob", 102, 3.5);

student1.displayInfo();
student1.setGPA(3.9);
```

